                <div class="newsCategoryContent">
                    <div>
	<p>
		AllGov reporter Sidney Finster has obtained a secret recording in which an unnamed Republican operative brags to a meeting of 2022 campaign workers that he invented the phrase &ldquo;Defund the Police.&rdquo;</p>
	<p>
		&nbsp;</p>
	<p>
		&ldquo;I paid some black guys to infiltrate the Black Lives Matter movement and start chanting, &lsquo;Defund the Police.&rsquo; It worked perfectly. It galvanized frightened whites to get out and vote against pro-crime Democrats. If Trump hadn&rsquo;t f---up the Covid issue, we would have swept both houses of Congress and kept the White House. But don&rsquo;t worry. We&rsquo;ll push the same phrase in the 2022 elections and this time we&rsquo;ll win everything. &lsquo;Democrats want to defund the police.&rsquo; Keep saying it over and over.&rdquo;</p>
	<p>
		&nbsp;</p>
	<p>
		One person asks, &ldquo;Do you really think that one issue is enough to win?&rdquo;</p>
	<p>
		&nbsp;</p>
	<p>
		The first speaker responds, &ldquo;Throw in stuff about immigration. That always works. Keep pushing that Democrats are soft on immigration and they&rsquo;re letting in terrorists, drug dealers, foreigners who take away American jobs and people who aren&rsquo;t white who are looking for a free ride.</p>
	<p>
		&nbsp;</p>
	<p>
		We&rsquo;re going to win everything. It&rsquo;s going to be great.&rdquo;</p>
	<p align="right">
		-David Wallechinsky</p>
	<p align="right">
		(satire)</p>
</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>

